cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 

- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses job placement decisions in hybrid HPC cloud environments, which involves distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses job traces from real supercomputing centers to run experiments, which is related to computational science. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper extends a machine learning-based predictor to work with data from the cluster scheduler, which falls under the scope of neural computing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses machine learning techniques to improve job placement decisions in HPC hybrid cloud environments. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a tool to make job placement decisions based on turnaround predictions, which involves designing algorithms and data structures.
